   "postDate": "2026-06-07T20:23:03.930Z",
   "rawMarkdown": "To my fellow Kagglers:\n\nChatGPT Plus — $20/month — is all you need for this competition.\n\nMy bio says I love ChatGPT and that I’m a devoted OpenAI fan. That is not joke. It is literally how I work.\n\nIn almost every chat, I either get help or learn something new from ChatGPT.\n\nWhen people ask me on LinkedIn how to improve their Kaggle performance, my answer is always simple:\n\nKeep asking ChatGPT.\n\nFor NeuroGolf, I used only ChatGPT Plus until I reached 7600. Only this week I finally upgrade to ChatGPT Pro, hoping to chase an even better result.\n\nAs Yiheng said, you can simply use ChatGPT in the web interface: copy-paste optimizations, run multiple tabs in parallel, and iterate constantly. That alone may be enough to get gold in this competition.\n\nIt is not fancy. But it works.\n\nYou only need trust ChatGPT. OpenAI is so nice and generous, as long as you use ChatGPT through the web app rather than the API, you can use it extensively without worrying about per-call costs.\n\n",
   "content": "<p>To my fellow Kagglers:</p>\n<p>ChatGPT Plus — $20/month — is all you need for this competition.</p>\n<p>My bio says I love ChatGPT and that I’m a devoted OpenAI fan. That is not joke. It is literally how I work.</p>\n<p>In almost every chat, I either get help or learn something new from ChatGPT.</p>\n<p>When people ask me on LinkedIn how to improve their Kaggle performance, my answer is always simple:</p>\n<p>Keep asking ChatGPT.</p>\n<p>For NeuroGolf, I used only ChatGPT Plus until I reached 7600. Only this week I finally upgrade to ChatGPT Pro, hoping to chase an even better result.</p>\n<p>As Yiheng said, you can simply use ChatGPT in the web interface: copy-paste optimizations, run multiple tabs in parallel, and iterate constantly. That alone may be enough to get gold in this competition.</p>\n<p>It is not fancy. But it works.</p>\n<p>You only need trust ChatGPT. OpenAI is so nice and generous, as long as you use ChatGPT through the web app rather than the API, you can use it extensively without worrying about per-call costs.</p>",
   "parent": {},
